---
description: How tests mock the upstream weather API
globs: "tests/**"
---

No test in this codebase makes a real network call.

- Tests that exercise `httpx` or `app/open_meteo.py` must use `respx`.
- Per-test mock payloads live in `tests/fixtures/open_meteo_responses.py`.
- Tests must clean up mocks between tests; use pytest fixtures instead of global monkeypatching.
- Replay/evaluation tests must not call Open-Meteo. Use synthetic readings or the committed
  climatology artifact. `scripts/evaluate.py` may fetch archive data only when manually run.
- Forecast-bust tests should provide synthetic stored forecasts and comparison pairs rather than
  relying on historical forecast APIs.

Generated tests that import `requests`, monkeypatch `httpx.get`, or hit a real URL are incorrect.
